text: Dhusaripara is a census town in Samserganj CD Block in Jangipur subdivision of Murshidabad district in the state of West Bengal, India. ==Geography== Dhusaripara is located at . ==Demographics== As per the 2011 Census of India, Dhusaripara had a total population of 17,800, of which 8,822 (50%) were males and 8,978 (50%) were females. Population below 6 years was 3,559. The total number of literates in Dhusaripara was 7,788 (54.69% of the population over 6 years). India census, Dhusaripara had a population of 12,117. Males constitute 50% of the population and females 50%. Dhusaripara has an average literacy rate of 30%, lower than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 39% and, female literacy is 21%. In Dhusaripara, 23% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Murshidabad district
